topPRs.title: op-supernode: Initial Chain Container Framework
topPRs.author: axelKingsley
topPRs.body: This initial PR for `op-supernode` introduces a core functionality: Chain Containers. Chain containers allow for multi-tenant Consensus Layer. The initial functionality of the `op-supernode` is to serve multiple CLs from a shared binary using shared resources. ## PR Breakdown - How to Review This PR is larger than I wanted it to be, but contains a solid unit of functionality: The ability to run multiple CLs inside a containerized system. The code breaks down into more reviewable sections: ### op-node - The only change to `op-node` is additional initialization to accept overloaded resources. This is used to create dependency-injected Virtual Nodes with shared resources. The overloads were made available in a prior PR and now being utilized. Additional refactor to the `cliiface` was added to expand a prior refactor I had done, where the `cli.Context` object is replaced. ### Acceptance Tests and Devstack - A new preset for 2 L2 networks bound by a Supernode is created - A new "TestL2CLAdvance Multiple" test which confirms two different networks advance from the same supernode. ### Supervisor A lot of Supervisor is CLi and Boilerplate, but here's why each component exists: - `supernode` is the primary Application Lifecycle, and manages Chain Containers - `chain_containers` hold chain-specific configuration and ensure a Virtual Node is always running - `virtual_node` wrap an underlying CL - `shared_clients` creates wrapped version of common resources (L1 clients) which the virtual nodes can't close - `http router` handles top level RPC and routes the calls down to the virtual nodes using a chainID supplied in the url - `virtual_flags` and `virtual_cli` namespaces the incoming CLI in order to implement a wrapped CLI Context which *appears* normal to the virtual nodes, allowing for 1:1 identical startup, including environment variables and defaults. ## Tests - Unit Test coverage on Virtual Node and Chain Container Lifecycle Management - Unit Test coverage on virtualized cli and flags - Unit test coverage on the http router - Acceptance Test coverage of advancing multiple chains - Manual testing of multi-chain syncing of `op-sepolia` and `base-sepolia` including RPC access: # Milestone 1 Closes/Satisfies[ Milestone 1](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/issues/17558)

topPRs.title: op-batcher: throttle config overhaul (pending-DA defaults, always-limit, step alignment)
topPRs.author: sashass1315
topPRs.body:
- Deprecate flag throttle.threshold-multiplier; keep backward-compat if --throttle.unsafe-da-bytes-upper-threshold is not set.
- Add throttle.tx-size-always-limit to cap tx size even at zero intensity.
- Add throttle.step-threshold-alignment (start|middle|end) to position the step threshold within the [lower, upper] range.
- Compute throttling intensity from pending DA bytes; still record unsafe DA bytes for visibility; update ratio metric to use pending bytes.
- Update defaults: lower=2,000,000 bytes (~1–2 channels), upper=lower20 (within 10–50x guidance).
- Controller: apply always-on tx limit at intensity 0; respect step alignment when selecting threshold.
- Docs: refresh op-batcher/throttling.md and op-batcher/readme.md with new flags, defaults, and guidance.
- Minor tests/docs comments adjusted for consistency.

Fix #16947

topPRs.title: feat(ai-contracts-test): add Slack notifications and bug fixes (v1.1.0)
topPRs.author: aliersh
topPRs.body:
This PR adds Slack notifications for PR creation and includes critical bug fixes for the AI Contract Test Maintenance System, bumping the version to 1.1.0.

## Changed

- **Slack Notifications**: Automatic notifications posted to AI PR review channel when PRs are created, including PR URL, test file, and reviewer guide link
- **Pagination Support**: Increased CircleCI pipeline fetching from 20 to 600 to ensure proper artifact exclusion and prevent duplicate work
- **Error Handling**: Job now exits with error code when Devin session blocks without PR, preventing artifacts from failed sessions
- **Prompt Improvements**: Enhanced constructor test organization and assertion guidelines with zero-tolerance rules
- **Documentation**: Updated all docs (README, runbook, [PR reviewer guide](https://www.notion.so/oplabs/AI-Contract-Test-Maintenance-System-PR-Reviewer-Guide-288f153ee16280478c0ed1adc5edd9f9?source=copy_link), [changelog](https://www.notion.so/oplabs/AI-Contracts-Test-Maintenance-System-Changelog-276f153ee16280b7b587d9648141f763?source=copy_link)) to reflect new features and version 1.1.0
